Package com.rb.nonbiz.jsonapi

Interface HasJsonApiDocumentation

All Known Implementing Classes:
ArithmeticProgressionJsonApiConverter, ClosedUnitFractionRangesJsonApiConverter, ConstantSequenceJsonApiConverter, CoordinatesJsonApiConverter, FlatSignedLinearCombinationJsonApiConverter, GeometricProgressionJsonApiConverter, HardAndSoftRangeJsonApiConverter, ImmutableDoubleIndexableArray2DJsonApiConverter, ImmutableIndexableArray1DJsonApiConverter, InstrumentTypeMapJsonApiConverter, MoneyFractionJsonApiConverter, MultiDimensionalArrayJsonApiConverter, RangeJsonApiConverter, RBCategoryMapJsonApiConverter, SimpleSequenceJsonApiConverter, StatisticalSummaryJsonApiConverter, WeightedBySignedFractionJsonApiConverter
public interface HasJsonApiDocumentation
Used by JSON API converter verb classes (NOT by the data classes they convert) to denote that a class has human-readable documentation (typically for developers) for its JSON-serialized version.

    • getJsonApiDocumentation

      JsonApiDocumentation getJsonApiDocumentation()

    • getAdditionalJsonApiDocumentation

      default java.util.Optional<RBSet<JsonApiDocumentation>> getAdditionalJsonApiDocumentation()
      In certain cases, a JSON API converter may do an in-line conversion of a data class or an enum, without a separate JSON API converter. This is particularly convenient in cases where whatever is being converted is simple, or (sometimes in the case of enums) only converted in a single location. To avoid needing to create a separate JSON API converter just so we can tie the relevant JsonApiDocumentation to an easy-to-find location (i.e. not those top-level lists of JSON entity documentation, such as RemainingJsonApiDocumentationLister in rbengine), we have this additional mechanism that allows a JSON API converter to supply additional documentation for whatever it's converting "in-line".

      We could have used a plain RBSet as a return type, and just return an empty set in most cases, but we like using Optional to make it explicit that the return value is not even applicable in certain cases.

    • getAllJsonApiDocumentation

      static RBSet<JsonApiDocumentation> getAllJsonApiDocumentation​(HasJsonApiDocumentation hasJsonApiDocumentation)
      Returns an RBSet consisting of the 'main' JsonApiDocumentation (which is required per this interface) and any additional ones, per getAdditionalJsonApiDocumentation().

      This is not marked default, because we can't make 'default final' methods on interfaces, so keeping it static will prevent others from accidentally overriding it.
